{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8a3bb878-6c2e-41f0-b01f-3dc6c853e930","content":"No, you don't need `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` anymore. In .NET 10, `dotnet test` uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform **natively by default** — that property was the opt-in for .NET 9 and is now a no-op.\n\nYou can safely remove it:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01QZneap3pQoetoee5xtwY9H","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Removing obsolete property"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_019MXTJg9qruGtFoSUe7cuoK","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-e939e5e4db1c4ae18c296e89b0423f09/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n","new_str":""},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-e939e5e4db1c4ae18c296e89b0423f09/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"433e6dc5-7b34-48f6-9e00-ae716068c6f4","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK (10.0.100) and is using MSTest with `EnableMSTestRunner` and `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`. They want to know if they still need the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property.\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) as the default test runner, so `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` is no longer needed. The property was required in .NET 9 and earlier to opt in to MTP support via `dotnet test`, but in .NET 10 it's the default behavior.\n\n\nI'll show them how to update their project file to remove the unnecessary property.","outputTokens":442,"requestId":"0837:1E21:6BB3BA4:781516B:69EABF2C"},"id":"70beed0b-a8ab-46b3-b996-6bd32c1c87a5","timestamp":"2026-04-24T00:54:11.116Z","parentId":"c400a961-12d2-4ce6-8868-15c8d1522827"}
